top-floor.name: top_dfra
label: Deline Family
Reading Area
top-floor.hover: The Deline Family Reading Area provides views of the downtown Denver skyline and front-range mountains beyond, with exhibit displays and various seating options.

top-floor.name: top_wpf
label: Writing Program
Faculty
top-floor.hover: The Writing Program offers renowned first-year writing classes, provides support for writing-intensive courses, leads workshops to help professors teach writing, and conducts research in writing, rhetoric and literacy.

top-floor.name: top_cfwlc
label: Center for World
Languages and
Cultures
top-floor.hover: The Center for World Languages and Cultures administers foreign language placement exams to undergraduate students registering for language courses.

top-floor.name: top_ds
label: Dean's Suite
top-floor.hover: The Dean's Suite houses offices and meeting space for professional staff with administrative roles in the library. These offices overlook the Buchtel Tower and the Holocaust Awareness and Social Action site.

top-floor.name: top_euc
label: Extended Use
Quiet Study
Area
top-floor.hover: The Extended Use Quiet Study Area offers an assigned carrel for one academic quarter to students writing a thesis or completing a major research project.

top-floor.name: top_frr
label: Faculty
Reading
Room
top-floor.hover: The Faculty Reading Room offers faculty a place to work, read, and collaborate.

top-floor.name: top_wtr
label: Wohlauer
Teleconference
Room      325
top-floor.hover: The Wohlauer Teleconferencing Room is acoustically designed and outfitted with state-of-the-art equipment to provide reliable teleconferencing capabilities to students, staff, or faculty.

top-floor.name: top_fsa
label: Gilbert Frank
Study Area
top-floor.hover: The study area funded by Margot Gilbert Frank and M Allan Frank, along with Recent Graduates of Colorado, provides seating and group study rooms near the DVD collection and viewing area.

top-floor.name: top_gr
label: Gottesfeld
Room
top-floor.hover: The Gottesfeld Room honors the important role of Marion Gottesfeld, who founded the Women's Library Association in 1956. Built-in cabinetry displays the collection of Artist Books - hand-made works of art

top-floor.name: top_loft
label: The Loft
top-floor.hover: The Loft hangs dramatically in the atrium, above the new book collection. It serves as a research seminar room with advanced technology that enables students and faculty to share information from their own devices.

top-floor.name: top_otl
label: Office of Teaching
and Learning
top-floor.hover: The Office of Teaching & Learning provides professional development to improve teaching practices, develops and supports state-of-the-art technology and web-based applications that enhance student learning and promotes innovation and collaboration.

top-floor.name: top_qrr
label: Quinette Family
Reading Room
top-floor.hover: The Quinette Family Reading Room offers 2,900 sq. ft. for reading and contemplation. It has beautiful views across Carnegie Green, a fireplace, display of the library’s valuable Ski Collection, plentiful windows, soft chairs and custom-built tables by DU alum Daniel Strawn.

top-floor.name: top_access_restroom1_pin
top-floor.hover: Gender neutral restroom, no door opener, accessibility features

main-floor.name: main_uts
label: IT @ DU
Technology
Services
main-floor.hover: The University Technology Services Help Center is staffed by specialized technicians who diagnose and repair hardware and software issues for students, faculty and staff.

main-floor.name: main_rc
label: Crossley
Research
Center
main-floor.hover: The Archibald M. and Helen M. Crossley Research Center provides expert research help to students, faculty, and staff at any stage of the research process.

main-floor.name: main_cc
label: Chan
Classroom
main-floor.hover: The Chan Classroom funded by the Boettcher Foundation is used by the Writing Program faculty to teach writing skills across all academic disciplines.

main-floor.name: main_er
label: Greg Kvistad
Special Events
Room
main-floor.hover: The Special Events Room can seat 200 people for academic events and presentations by students and faculty. When not in use for an event, the space is set with tables and chairs as an open study area.

main-floor.name: main_dmc
label: Digital
Media
Center
main-floor.hover: The Digital Media Center is a brand-new service to DU, serving as a digital media editing facility with equipment, software and staff support.

main-floor.name: main_hr
label: Herold Research
Instruction Room
main-floor.hover: The Virginia Herold Research Instruction Room serves thousands of students each year with classes and workshops in navigating the abundant resources of the University Library, including nearly 1,000 databases.

main-floor.name: main_mc
label: Math
Center
main-floor.hover: The Math Center provides drop-in assistance for Algebra, Trigonometry, Business Calculus, and Calculus I-III classes, including homework review and help preparing for exams.

main-floor.name: main_nsr
label: Nikki's
Study
Room
main-floor.hover: Small Group Study Room 212 - Nikki's Study Room

main-floor.name: main_sec
label: Science and
Engineering
Center
main-floor.hover: The Science and Engineering Center is a collaborative space staffed by undergraduate and graduate learning assistants (LAs) trained to assist students with first and second year biology, chemistry, physics, and engineering lecture and laboratory courses.

main-floor.name: main_wc
label: Shopneck
Family
Writing
Center
main-floor.hover: The Shopneck Family Writing Center offers one-on-one consultations, providing writers comprehensive and collaborative advice on writing.

main-floor.name: main_main_access_restroom1_pin
main-floor.hover: Gender neutral restroom, no door opener, accessibility features

main-floor.name: main_lenddesk
label: Perlmutter
Lending
Desk
main-floor.hover: The Jordon and Essie Perlmutter and Family Lending Services Desk provides help locating and checking out books and materials.

main-floor.name: main_resdesk
label: Research
Desk
main-floor.hover: Click to ask a research question

main-floor.name: main_complab
label: Open Computer Lab
main-floor.hover: Computers are available in Main Library for members of the University community, but some have particular uses.  Visitors may access computers under certain conditions.

main-floor.name: main_cafe
label: Front
Porch
Cafe
main-floor.hover: The Front Porch Cafe, located in the Anderson Academic Commons, offers not only coffee, smoothies, tea, and desserts, but also a wide array of healthy breakfast and lunch selections.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_fgs
label: Family
Group
Study
bottom-floor.hover: In response to requests from graduate students, the Anderson Academic Commons has a Family Study Room where students may bring their children while they use the library, and the kids are comfortable with toys and kidsized furniture while Mom or Dad studies.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_frr
label: Fogel
Family
Reading
Room
bottom-floor.hover: DU has long had impressive Special Collections, and with the Ida and Max Fogel Family Reading Room, we now have an appropriate place where scholars and students may review and conduct research using these rare and valuable materials.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_gfeuc
label: Gilbertson Family
Quiet Study Room
bottom-floor.hover: An anonymous donor funded the Quiet Study Room where acoustic engineering limits noise from other areas of the Academic Commons and from Evans Avenue so that students may easily focus on their assignments.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_sc
label: Special
Collections
bottom-floor.hover: Special Collections are climate controlled, locked and supervised. With Special Collections are offices for the University Historian, the curators of the University Archives and the Ira M. and Peryle Hayutin Beck Memorial Archives of Rocky Mountain Jewish History, and an exhibit preparation room.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_ssr
label: Schayer
Seminar
Room
bottom-floor.hover: The Charles M. and Faye G. Schayer Seminar Room serves as a classroom for professors who bring students to work with primary sources. Imagine holding an important historic document or the costume of a famous dancer! The Schayer Room may also be used by archivists, historians and librarians for meetings.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_vcs
label: Video
Creation
Studio
bottom-floor.hover: The Video Creation Studio is a professional recording studio that can be used by DU faculty and staff with very little video production experience.

bottom-floor.name: bottom_access_restroom1_pin
bottom-floor.hover: Gender neutral restroom, no door opener, accessibility features

bottom-floor.name: bottom_stacks_label
label: Penrose
Collection
Main
Stacks
bottom-floor.hover: The Penrose Collection includes all of the books and materials belonging to the University Libraries. In honor of the family that funded El Pomar Foundation, and which, in turn, provided the funds not only to build DU’s former library but to make major acquisitions of important resources, we have named the collection for Spencer and Julie Penrose, the library’s forty-year namesake
